U||Waste Paper
U||A Poem of Profound Insignificance
U||By H. P. Lovecraft
U||Πἀντα γἐλως καἱ πἀντα κὀνις καἱ πἀντα τὁ μηδἐν
U||Out of the reaches of illimitable light
U||The blazing planet grew, and forc’d to life
U||Unending cycles of progressive strife
U||And strange mutations of undying light
U||And boresome books, than hell’s own self more trite
U||And thoughts repeated and become a blight,
U||And cheap rum-hounds with moonshine hootch made tight,
U||And quite contrite to see the flight of fright so bright
U||I used to ride my bicycle in the night
U||With a dandy acetylene lantern that cost $3.00
U||In the evening, by the moonlight, you can hear those darkies singing
U||Meet me tonight in dreamland . . . BAH
U||I used to sit on the stairs of the house where I was born
U||After we left it but before it was sold
U||And play on a zobo with two other boys.
U||We called ourselves the Blackstone Military Band
U||Won’t you come home, Bill Bailey, won’t you come home?
U||In the spring of the year, in the silver rain
U||When petal by petal the blossoms fall
U||And the mocking birds call
U||And the whippoorwill sings, Marguerite.
U||The first cinema show in our town opened in 1906
U||At the old Olympic, which was then call’d Park,
U||And moving beams shot weirdly thro’ the dark
U||And spit tobacco seldom hit the mark.
U||Have you read Dickens’ American Notes?
U||My great-great-grandfather was born in a white house
U||Under green trees in the country
U||And he used to believe in religion and the weather.
U||“Shantih, shantih, shantih” . . . Shanty House
U||Was the name of a novel by I forget whom
U||Published serially in the All-Story Weekly
U||Before it was a weekly. Advt.
U||Disillusion is wonderful, I’ve been told,
U||And I take quinine to stop a cold
U||But it makes my ears ring . . . always ring . . .
U||Always ringing in my ears . . .
U||It is the ghost of the Jew I murdered that Christmas day
U||Because he played “Three O’Clock in the Morning” in the flat above me.
U||Three O’Clock in the morning, I’ve danc’d the whole night through,
U||Dancing on the graves in the graveyard
U||Where life is buried; life and beauty
U||Life and art and love and duty
U||Ah, there, sweet cutie.
U||Stung!
U||Out of the night that covers me
U||Black as the pit from pole to pole
U||I never quote things straight except by accident.
U||Sophistication! Sophistication!
