U||The Rose of England
U||By H. P. Lovecraft
U||At morn the rosebud greets the sun
U||And sheds the evening dew,
U||Expanding ere the day is done,
U||In bloom of radiant hue;
U||And when the sun his rest hath found,
U||Rose-petals strow the garden round!
U||Thus that blest Isle that owns the Rose
U||From mist and darkness came,
U||A million glories to disclose,
U||And spread BRITANNIA’S name;
U||And ere Life’s Sun shall leave the blue,
U||ENGLAND shall reign the whole world thro’!
