U||Sunset
U||By H. P. Lovecraft
U||The cloudless day is richer at its close;
U||A golden glory settles on the lea;
U||Soft, stealing shadows hint of cool repose
U||To mellowing landscape, and to calming sea.
U||And in that nobler, gentler, lovelier light,
U||The soul to sweeter, loftier bliss inclines;
U||Freed form the noonday glare, the favour’d sight
U||Increasing grace in earth and sky divines.
U||But ere the purest radiance crowns the green,
U||Or fairest lustre fills th’ expectant grove,
U||The twilight thickens, and the fleeting scene
U||Leaves but a hallow’d memory of love!
