U||On Reading Lord Dunsany’s
U||Book of Wonder
U||By H. P. Lovecraft
U||The hours of night unheeded fly,
U||And in the grate the embers fade;
U||Vast shadows one by one pass by
U||In silent daemon cavalcade.
U||But still the magic volume holds
U||The raptur’d eye in realms apart,
U||And fulgent sorcery enfolds
U||The willing mind and eager heart.
U||The lonely room no more is there—
U||For to the sight in pomp appear
U||Temples and cities pois’d in air
U||And blazing glories—sphere on sphere.
U|| 
