U||Life’s Mystery
U||By H. P. Lovecraft
U||Life! Ah, Life!
U||What may this fluorescent pageant mean?
U||Who can the evanescent object glean?
U||He that is dead is the key of Life—
U||Gone is the symbol, deep is the grave!
U||Man is a breath, and Life is the fire;
U||Birth is death, and silence the choir.
U||Wrest from the aeons the heart of gold!
U||Tear from the fabric the threads that are old!
U||Life! Ah, Life!
U||—L. Phillips Howard
