U||In a Sequester’d Providence Churchyard
U||Where Once Poe Walk’d
U||By H. P. Lovecraft
U||Eternal brood the shadows on this ground,
U||Dreaming of centuries that have gone before;
U||Great elms rise solemnly by slab and mound,
U||Arch’d high above a hidden world of yore.
U||Round all the scene a light of memory plays,
U||And dead leaves whisper of departed days,
U||Longing for sights and sounds that are no more.
U||Lonely and sad, a spectre glides along
U||Aisles where of old his living footsteps fell;
U||No common glance discerns him, tho’ his song
U||Peals down thro’ time with a mysterious spell:
U||Only the few who sorcery’s secret know
U||Espy amidst these tombs the shade of Poe.
U|| 
