U||[Christmas Greetings to Felis
U||(Frank Belknap Long’s cat)]
U||By H. P. Lovecraft
U||Haughty Sphinx, whose amber eyes
U||Hold the secrets of the skies,
U||As thou ripplest in thy grace,
U||Round the chairs and chimney-place,
U||Scorn on thy patrician face:
U||Hiss not harsh, nor use thy claws
U||On the hand that gives applause—
U||Good-will only doth abide
U||In these lines at Christmastide!
