U||Astrophobos
U||By H. P. Lovecraft
U||In the midnight heavens burning
U||Thro’ ethereal deeps afar,
U||Once I watch’d with restless yearning
U||An alluring, aureate star;
U||Ev’ry eye aloft returning,
U||Gleaming nigh the Arctic car.
U||Mystic waves of beauty blended
U||With the gorgeous golden rays;
U||Phantasies of bliss descended
U||In a myrrh’d Elysian haze;
U||And in lyre-born chords extended
U||Harmonies of Lydian lays.
U||There (thought I) lies scenes of pleasure,
U||Where the free and blessed dwell,
U||And each moment bears a treasure
U||Freighted with a lotus-spell,
U||And there floats a liquid measure
U||From the lute of Israfel.
U||There (I told myself) were shining
U||Worlds of happiness unknown,
U||Peace and Innocence entwining
U||By the Crowned Virtue’s throne;
U||Men of light, their thoughts refining
U||Purer, fairer, than our own.
U||Thus I mus’d, when o’er the vision
U||Crept a red delirious change;
U||Hope dissolving to derision,
U||Beauty to distortion strange;
U||Hymnic chords in weird collision,
U||Spectral sights in endless range.
U||Crimson burn’d the star of sadness
U||As behind the beams I peer’d;
U||All was woe that seem’d but gladness
U||Ere my gaze with truth was sear’d;
U||Cacodaemons, mir’d with madness,
U||Thro’ the fever’d flick’ring leer’d.
U||Now I know the fiendish fable
U||That the golden glitter bore;
U||Now I shun the spangled sable
U||That I watch’d and lov’d before;
U||But the horror, set and stable,
U||Haunts my soul for evermore.
U|| 
