U||Arcadia
U||By H. P. Lovecraft
U||By Head Balledup
U||O give me the life of the village,
U||Uninhibited, free, and sweet;
U||The place where the arts all flourish,
U||Grove Court and Christopher Street.
U||I am sick of the old conventions,
U||And critics who will not praise,
U||So sing ho for the open spaces,
U||And aesthetes with kindly ways.
U||Here every bard is a genius,
U||And artists are Raphaels,
U||And above the roofs of Patchin Place
U||The Muse of Talent dwells.
